details: Bananas are a great source of vitamin B6, which helps your body produce serotonin.
Spinach is high in iron, essential for oxygen transport in the blood.
Salmon is rich in omega-3 fatty acids, which support heart and brain health.
Carrots are packed with beta-carotene, which the body converts into vitamin A for good vision.
Greek yogurt contains probiotics that promote a healthy gut microbiome.
Almonds are an excellent source of vitamin E, an antioxidant that helps protect cells.
Eggs provide high-quality protein and contain all nine essential amino acids.
Avocados are loaded with monounsaturated fats that can help reduce bad cholesterol.
Quinoa is a complete protein, meaning it contains all essential amino acids.
Blueberries are rich in antioxidants, which help fight inflammation and oxidative stress.
